Gauzelin is a catholic saint died in 962.Born of a noble family of frankish, he was a notary of the royal chancery when the king, Charles the Simple appointed as bishop of Toul. It is sacred bishop of Toul, march 17, 922. After the devastation caused by the invasions of the Danish and Hungarian, Gauzelin falls within his diocese, the reform of the monasteries and built new ones. He died on September 7, 962, after forty years of episcopate. He founded the abbey of (Bouxières-aux-Dames in 935 or 936.Several objects belonging to him, a évangéliaire, a chalice with its paten, a comb, liturgical, and episcopal ring, were joined in 1803 the treasury of the cathedral of Nancy. Gauzelin
